!!!
%html.not-found
  %head
    %meta{:charset => 'utf-8'}
    %link{:href => '/stylesheets/compiled/main.css', :rel => 'stylesheet'}
    %title 404 — Page Not Found
  %body
    %h1 This document is missing
    %p
      I couldn't find the page you were looking for. Some links have moved recently,
      so you might have better luck changing the domain to
      <a href="http://burgestrand.tumblr.com" id="tumblr">burgestrand.tumblr.com</a>
    
    %h2 Still can’t find it?
    %p
      Then it’s likely that it has vanished into oblivion and will never be found.
      My main page still remains at <a href="http://burgestrand.se/">burgestrand.se/</a>
      though, so all is not lost.
    
    :javascript
      var tumblr = document.getElementById("tumblr");
      var loc = window.location.pathname.toString();
      tumblr.href = tumblr.href + loc.replace(/^\//, '');
      tumblr.innerHTML = tumblr.innerHTML + loc;
    
    // observerapp.com
    <script type="text/javascript" src="http://www.observerapp.com/record.js"></script>
